						               													<description>Quirky is an abstract strategy board game of luck (of the draw), placement (strategy), stacking and points accumulation on a triangular wooden board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Based on the number '3' and designed for three players by Games Above Board, the (Canadian) publisher states Quirky may also be played by two players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has a colour (which may change during the game) and, taking turns, draws different-shaped pieces at random from a bag - placing them on the board regardless of the owner yet being careful not to help the opponent(s) nor hinder their own strategy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Should the colours change, players retain their points scored and continue playing against what was previously their own color pieces and strategy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pieces may be placed 3-high and top pieces may be removed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Placement or exposure of 3 same-colour pieces in a triangle scores 3 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object is to be the first to score 45 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
